A_n = \dfrac {(n+2)^{2n}}{(n^2-n-6)^n}
A_n=\frac{(n+2)^{2n}}{(n^2-n-6)^n}=\left(\frac{(n+2)(n+2)}{(n+2)(n-3)}\right)^n
=\left(\frac{n+2}{n-3}\right)^n=\left(\frac{1+2/n}{1-3/n}\right)^n
a_n=\frac{(n+2)^{2n}}{(n^2-n-6)^n}=\frac{(1+\frac 4 n+\frac 4{n^2})^{n}}{(1-\frac1n-\frac6{n^2})^n}
\log(a_n)=n\left(\log\left(1+\frac 4 n+\frac 4{n^2}\right)-\log\left(1-\frac1n-\frac6{n^2}\right)\right)\sim_\infty n\left(\frac 4 n+\frac 1n\right)=5
\lim_{n\to\infty}a_n=e^5
A_n = \left( (n+2)^2/(n^2-n-6) \right)^n = \left( (n+2)/(n-3) \right)^n = \left( (n-3+5)/(n-3)\right)^n = \left(1 + 5/(n-3)\right)^n
